[John 1:17](../../../bib/kjv/joh001.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">joh 1:17</span></span>

grace

Grace. Summary:

\(1\) Grace is "the kindness and love of God our Saviour toward man. . .
Not by works of righteousness which we have done" ([Tit
3:4](../../../bib/kjv/tit003.htm#004).md); ([Tit
3:5](../../../bib/kjv/tit003.htm#005).md).

It is, therefore, constantly set in contrast to law, under which God
demands righteousness from man, as, under grace, he gives righteousness
to man ([Rom 3:21](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#021).md); ([Rom
3:22](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#022).md); ([Rom
8:4](../../../bib/kjv/rom008.htm#004).md); ([Plm
3:9](../../../bib/kjv/plm003.htm#009).md). Law is connected with Moses and
works; grace with Christ and faith; ([Joh
1:17](../../../bib/kjv/joh001.htm#017).md); ([Rom
10:4-10](../../../bib/kjv/rom010.htm#004).md). Law blesses the good; grace
saves the bad; ([Exo 19:5](../../../bib/kjv/exo019.htm#005).md); ([Eph
2:1-9](../../../bib/kjv/eph002.htm#001).md). Law demands that blessings be
earned; grace is a free gift; ([Deu
28:1-6](../../../bib/kjv/deu028.htm#001).md); ([Eph
2:8](../../../bib/kjv/eph002.htm#008).md); ([Rom
4:4](../../../bib/kjv/rom004.htm#004).md); ([Rom
4:5](../../../bib/kjv/rom004.htm#005).md).

\(2\) As a dispensation, grace begins with the death and resurrection of
Christ ([Rom 3:24-26](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#024).md); ([Rom
3:4](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#004).md); ([Rom
3:24](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#024).md); ([Rom
3:25](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#025).md). The point of testing is no
longer legal obedience as the condition of salvation, but acceptance or
rejection of Christ, with good works as a fruit of salvation, ([Joh
1:12](../../../bib/kjv/joh001.htm#012).md); ([Joh
1:13](../../../bib/kjv/joh001.htm#013).md); ([Joh
3:36](../../../bib/kjv/joh003.htm#036).md); ([Mat
21:37](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#037).md); ([Mat
22:24](../../../bib/kjv/mat022.htm#024).md); ([Joh
15:22](../../../bib/kjv/joh015.htm#022).md); ([Joh
15:25](../../../bib/kjv/joh015.htm#025).md); ([Heb
1:2](../../../bib/kjv/heb001.htm#002).md); ([Jo1
5:10-12](../../../bib/kjv/jo1005.htm#010).md). The immediate result of this
testing was the rejection of Christ by the Jews, and His crucifixion by
Jew and Gentile ([Act 4:27](../../../bib/kjv/act004.htm#027).md). The
predicted end of the testing of man under grace is the apostasy of the
professing church:

(see "Apostasy"

(See Scofield) - ([Ti2 3:1](../../../bib/kjv/ti2003.htm#001).md); ([Ti2
3:1-8](../../../bib/kjv/ti2003.htm#001).md);

and the resultant apocalyptic judgments.

\(3\) Grace has a twofold manifestation: in salvation ([Rom
3:24](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#024).md) and in the walk and service of
the saved ([Rom 6:15](../../../bib/kjv/rom006.htm#015).md).

